                                    Ward E Councilperson Eleana Little

                                    Term of Office:
                                    First Elected To Council: Dec. 2, 2025 
                                    Current Term Expires: January 14, 2030

                                    (201) 547-5315
                                    ELittle@jcnj.org

                                    Council Aide: Grace Perez
                                    (201) 547-5283
                                    GPerez@jcnj.org
                                    Biography
                                    Eleana Little is a neighbor with progressive values and a passion for public service. Prior to her election, Eleana was an active community advocate in downtown Jersey City, serving as President of the Harsimus Cove Association. Professionally, Eleana is an environmental engineer with degrees from Rutgers University and UC Berkeley and a decade of experience across both the public and private sectors. Originally from Central Jersey, she first moved to Jersey City 12 years ago, and currently lives in downtown Jersey City with her fianc and their two dogs. She is honored to have the opportunity to serve the people of Jersey City on the City Council.
